MODULES
Exercise - Write a function called find_max, this function will take a list and return the largest number in that list.
Extract the function and put in a module called utils, then import the utils module into the current module and call find_max.
Get the result and print it on the terminal.
numbers = [10,3, 6, 2]
max = numbers[0]
for item in numbers:
    if item > max:
        max = item
print(max)


